# Getting Started

## Installation

bcachefs is distributed as a DKMS module (like ZFS). Your distribution's
bcachefs-tools package includes everything you need: the kernel module and
userspace tools.

**Arch, NixOS:** Install bcachefs-tools from your package manager - you're done.

**Debian, Ubuntu:**

    sudo install -d -m 0755 /etc/apt/keyrings
    wget -qO- https://apt.bcachefs.org/apt.bcachefs.org.asc | sudo tee /etc/apt/keyrings/apt.bcachefs.org.asc > /dev/null
    sudo chmod 0644 /etc/apt/keyrings/apt.bcachefs.org.asc
    # Fingerprint: EA483B991020C72A8A5035ADA0620B5E0E01C1DD
    sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/apt.bcachefs.org.sources > /dev/null <<EOF
    Types: deb deb-src
    URIs: https://apt.bcachefs.org/unstable/
    # Or replace unstable with your distro's release name
    Suites: bcachefs-tools-release
    Components: main
    Signed-By: /etc/apt/keyrings/apt.bcachefs.org.asc
    EOF
    sudo apt update
    sudo apt install bcachefs-tools

**Fedora:**

    sudo dnf copr enable ngompa/bcachefs
    sudo dnf install bcachefs-tools

**OpenSUSE:** See [[https://build.opensuse.org/package/show/filesystems:bcachefs:release/bcachefs]]

## Basic usage

Format and mount a single device:

    bcachefs format /dev/sda1
    mount -t bcachefs /dev/sda1 /mnt

## Multi-device filesystem

For a tiered setup with sda1 (fast SSD) caching sdb1 (slow HDD):

    bcachefs format /dev/sd[ab]1 \
        --foreground_target /dev/sda1 \
        --promote_target /dev/sda1 \
        --background_target /dev/sdb1
    mount -t bcachefs /dev/sda1:/dev/sdb1 /mnt

Writes buffer to the fast device and migrate to the slow device in the
background. Hot data gets promoted back to the fast device automatically.

For systemd mounts of multi-device filesystems, use `bcachefs wait-devices`
or the packaged `bcachefs-wait-devices@.service` template so the mount waits
until all member devices are visible.

The Debian/Ubuntu repository has two suites:

* `bcachefs-tools-release` - latest release
* `bcachefs-tools-snapshot` - latest `git master` snapshot

## Next steps

See `bcachefs format --help` for all options, or read the full
[[User manual|https://bcachefs.org/bcachefs-principles-of-operation.pdf]] for detailed documentation
on all features.
